Text.Value: Seems like you're right where you're supposed to be.
Show her a Night Orchid, to jog her memory.
Lady Shar's blessings be upon you.
Ah, my apparent long-lost acquaintance. Here to wax lyrical about all the good times we didn't share?
Seems like you're right where you're supposed to be.
We journeyed together. Survived all sorts of perils.
Lovers? I think you must have me mistaken for someone with no taste.
Find someplace else to stand. You may meet with an unfortunate accident if you linger here.
Shadowheart, it's me - [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53]. You know me.
I'm sorry. I did this to you.
No. Should I?
We were lovers.
I take it you're here at the Mother Superior's invitation - no outsider would have made it this far without permission.
Don't you recognise me at all?
Oh is that so? That's quite an imagination you have - are you a bard, granted entry to our Grotto in order to regale us with ballads and tall tales?

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused/sceptical. Does not remember the player after a memory wipe.

Text.Value: I don't have a favourite flower. Perhaps there's another Shadowheart out there, that you're confusing me with.
Use your tadpole. Seek a connection with her.
Curious, this one. They seem a touch confused. Mother Superior must have some use for them.
As long as you show Lady Shar all due respect, you'll be treated accordingly. Now, unless there's something else...
Try to read her thoughts.
They're your favourites. Don't you recognise them?
Forget it. In fact, it seems you already have.
What the...? The Hells do you think you're doing?!
Walk away - now. Try anything like that again and you'll find your guest privileges can be revoked very quickly.
I'm an honoured guest. Be sure to remember that.
You're a strange one. On your way, then.
Dark Lady as my witness, I have no idea what you're talking about. I think we're done here.
Pretty, whatever it is. But if you're seeking to court me, I'm afraid I'm busy.
*This is no act. You are an utter stranger to her. The memories you shared with her will die with you.*
I'm sorry. I did this to you.
I've never clapped eyes on you in my life. Did one of the others put you up to this? Tell you my name and see if you could get a rise out of me?
Of course I am. Now unless you've any other dazzling insights to share, I think we're done here.
Let's spare the both of us the bother, shall we? Whoever you think I am... I'm not her.

Synopsis: If the player sold Shadowheart out to Viconia. Shadowheart will have been mind-wiped and no longer remember the player when they bump into her later at the Sharran Grotto.
